programme.desc: It's one thing to have a mega kitchen that feeds thousands, but a traveling mega kitchen that feeds thousands is quite another. Watch how ISKCON's Yatra Kitchen travels across India, setting up almost overnight to feed Krishna-devotees from all over the world.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna S7E4
programme.desc: It's tournament time in Gloucester and when inexperienced fishermen - or googans as the commercial fleet refer to them - crowd the water, the fleet has to fight through additional aggravating obstacles standing in their way of earning a paycheck. While googans wreak havoc with their carelessness, some commercial boats will manage to land fish against the odds while others will go home empty-handed. And one boat will score the biggest payday so far this season, but not without a fight.

programme.title: Lost Treasures of Egypt E1
programme.desc: In this episode, archaeologists unlock the mysteries of Egypt's most famous pharaoh, Tutankhamun. We unearth a long lost box of treasures from inside Tutankhamun's tomb. New technology reveals why this boy kings resting place remained hidden from tomb robbers for thousands of years and we join the team who are tasked with transporting Tutankhamun's priceless treasures, on a one in a lifetime journey through the desert. Whilst a team of archaeologists make a new discovery of a lifetime when they open a 4000-year-old tomb.

programme.title: Lost Treasures of Egypt E2
programme.desc: Archaeologists investigate one of the greatest female pharaohs in history - Hatshepsut. A team digging around her iconic temple find clues about her powerful reign. A rare discovery inside one of Hatshepsut's ancient quarries sparks an investigation which leads to the magnificent temple of Karnak.. And one archaeologist discovers dramatic evidence about the lives of women in ancient Egypt whilst excavating mummy parts from inside an ancient tomb.

programme.title: Drain The Oceans S2E14
programme.desc: Drain the Oceans unlocks the secrets of how the Japanese Empire rose to power in the Pacific and how it harnessed superior technology turning that devastating firepower against the Allies. It reveals hidden secrets of a catastrophic attack on Australia that gave Japan control of the region and how its extraordinary tactics brought the British Empire to its knees.

programme.title: One Strange Rock E3
programme.desc: Earth protects itself from the sun. The David and Goliath story of Earths relationship with its greatest threat, our seemingly benign Sun. The Sun is the big violent boss of the Solar System throwing out devastating particles and deadly radiation. Without several shields, one generated by our unique planetary core, another by our atmosphere, and a third by our interconnected weather systems, life on Earth would never have survived.

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S2E4
programme.desc: It is story of journey, travelled by tribal children from interiors of Odisha to a national level and the world stage. It is a world's largest tribal school. This is also an inspiring & uplifting human story about empowering the poorest of the poor. Feeding their dreams with education and a full plate...is the Kalinga institute of social sciences. Presenting the MEGA facts of the kitchen, 25,000 children are fed 3 meals a day (approx. 76000 in total) in a 10,000-capacity dining hall on an 80 acre campus.

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E10
programme.desc: Now with fossil fuels becoming increasingly sparse, one company is trying to change the way we commute; this is the story behind the world's first fully electric premium sedan – the Tesla Model S. Tesla's electrical experts in Fremont, CA are gearing up for mass production in a groundbreaking new Mega Factory – but will the Model S take the world by storm?

programme.title: No Man Left Behind E1
programme.desc: During the Battle of Mogadishu, a squad of US Rangers and Delta Force including Keni Thomas and Randy Ramaglia, rope down from Black Hawk helicopter for a mission to capture two top lieutenants of rebel leader Mohamed Aidid but their Hawk gets shot down by outgunned ground troops. Another Black Hawk flies in to help but is hit and downed, putting pilot Mike Durant in captive for 11 days.

programme.title: The Story Of God With Morgan Freeman S3E4
programme.desc: Sin is a part of the human condition. But can we conquer it? Morgan Freeman travels the world, from California to Italy to Vietnam, to understand how different faiths think of and deal with sin. He'll learn about the bloody Medieval practice of self-flagellation, the mysterious Sin Eaters, and the Confucian view of sin. He'll also meet a man who is trying to atone for his years as an executioner.

programme.title: Underworld, Inc. S2E4
programme.desc: We follow the dirty drug dollars from American trap houses to wholesalers and transporters, funneling billions into Mexico's money laundering cycle. US authorities are closing in on cartel cash. If drug lords want their narco cheddar cleaned and moved into the banking system, they have to get it to Mexico.

programme.desc: There's only forty-eight hours left in the Outer Banks Bluefin season, and while a Southern boat leads the fleet, one Northern vessel continues their assault for the top earning spot. With final paychecks on the line, big fish on the hook and so little time, a fight to the finish is the only guarantee.

programme.title: The Hidden Kingdoms Of China E4
programme.desc: China's vast grasslands are a hard place to survive. Battered by ferocious and unpredictable storms throughout the year, the inhabitants of these grasslands have to be adaptable and tenacious to survive. During the short three-month window of summer, the plains residents have to race against time to raise their young before the onset of autumn and winter begin.

programme.title: Nazi Megastructures: America's War E6
programme.desc: Spring 1944. An allied invasion of Hitler's Fortress Europe is inevitable, and under the leadership of distinguished commander Field Marshall Erwin Rommel, the Germans begin a comprehensive programme to turn coastal areas into killing zones. But they still have no idea where and when the invasion will come, and in a fascinating game of cat and mouse, the Allies keep them guessing all the way up to 6th June 1944 - D-Day.

programme.title: Gok's Chinese Takeaway E6
programme.desc: In this final episode of Gok's Chinese Takeaway, Gok Wan returns home to London to discover Westernized version of Cantonese cuisine like Chop Suey, Crispy Duck and Sweet and Sour Pork. Finally, Gok draws on the food and culinary influences from his travels throughout Europe, Asia and Australia in order to create his ultimate celebratory feast of Chinese food from around the world.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna S7E5
programme.desc: It's week seven of fishing and boats are teaming up to share information, in a bid to catch more fish. But when Paul Hebert, captain of the fleet's current top-earning boat, Wicked Pissah, takes pity on Captain TJ Ott of Hot Tuna, who have struggled to catch for more than a week, Paul's decision to help them just might backfire on him.

programme.title: Science of Stupid S7E5
programme.desc: In this episode we learn the science behind the fails, when riding a horse through water, steering a radio-controlled plane and underestimating the power of ocean tides.

programme.title: Street Genius S1E3
programme.desc: Tim Shaw’s scientific experiments take in everything from Hollywood-style car chases to bottle caps and bicycle wheels, as he exposes how the world works. Big bangs are on the agenda as Tim attempts to blow up his pickup truck. For the finale, he will attempt to keep his car off the ground using the power of household vacuum cleaners.

programme.title: Street Genius S1E4
programme.desc: Tim Shaw, our guide the to the sensational world of science, creates lightning, passes a live wire through a pickle, blasts through ice blocks, and attempts to create instant fried turkey from frozen. Along the way the people he meets and the viewers are invited to guess the outcome of his incredible experiments.

programme.title: One Strange Rock E4
programme.desc: Our rock is special - it's alive. Though the building blocks of life are common across the universe, life is rare. So what is it about planet earth that sets it apart? What dynamic forces, what coincidences took a bunch of dead ingredients and transformed them into something as insanely intricate as Life? And if happened here could it happen elsewhere?

programme.title: Nick Baker's Eco Malaysia
programme.desc: British naturalist, Nick Baker, travels to South East Asia to embark on a unique eco-adventure in the Malaysian Peninsula - one of the most bio-diverse landscapes on the planet. His journey begins in the 130 million-year-old Belum-Temengor rainforest, and then he travels to the lush valley of Lenggong to explore the caves of Gua Gunung Runtuh before trying his hand at elephant caretaking.

programme.title: Nazi Megastructures S4E2
programme.desc: From Monte Cassino to San Pietro and ultimately the defence of Rome, this is the amazing story of one of the toughest defensive structures that the Nazis ever conceived. The Allies thought an advance from the south would be a quick way to bring down the Nazis, but they were wrong. Hitler, determined to defend every inch of ground, ordered a series of defensive lines stretching across the entire Italian peninsula, stalling the Allies' advance into the Third Reich for almost two years.

programme.title: Drain The Oceans S2E15
programme.desc: Drain the Oceans unlocks the secrets of how the Roman Empire controlled the seas of the Ancient world and how it harnessed the power of volcanoes to defy nature itself. It reveals the extraordinary secrets of one of the oldest shipwrecks in the world, and unearths a port lost for centuries under Italian soil.

programme.title: Lawless Island Alaska Compilations S2E5
programme.desc: One time city girl, Mary's story breaks the mold. Living alone in Alaska is tough and the learning curve is steep. Luckily, she has the help of the Lawless Island community to help her stand on her own two feet.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S8E7
programme.desc: A failed businessman, plumber Paul Keanys desperately looks for opportunities to make ends meet for his family. Acquainted with a local drug dealer, Paul agrees to smuggle six kilos of cocaine from Venezuela back to Dublin. But when he is stopped at the airport in Caracas, Paul unfortunately lives to regret his decision.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna S7E1
programme.desc: The Gloucester, Massachusetts's bluefin tuna fishing fleet is back for another season with the biggest paydays they've ever seen and the most toxic voyages in Wicked Tuna history. FV-Tuna.Com is determined to reclaim the title of Champion of the fleet. With his returning, trusty crew, Captain Dave Carraro plans to start this season by catching the first fish and not stop until he has brought in more fish and more profit than any other boat. But, he'll have stiff competition this year fishing against the best of the best in New England. All boats are returning: as the second place finisher last season, Pinwheel is on a mission to dethrone the champion; Hot Tuna has a renewed sense of purpose, longing to shatter their lackluster reputation; Hard Merchandise is expanding its family operation with a new crew-member ready to make a profit; Wicked Pissah needs to retain and surpass its successful previous season; and Fish Hawk desperately needs to recover from an embarrassing and u.

programme.title: The Hidden Kingdoms Of China E5
programme.desc: Meet China's most affectionate and vocal monkeys in the remote, seasonal forests of Central China. These mountain forests and all who live here, experience unpredictable and harsh weather in a land that can be covered in snow for 4 months of the year. Follow the journey of a baby Golden snub-nosed monkey during the first year of her life as she learns all about her forest home and battles the elements to survive.

programme.title: Scrapyard Supercar E6
programme.desc: Ralph and his 2 teams of guerrilla mechanics take on Shane's Land Rover Discovery in a daunting hill climb.

programme.title: The Witch Doctor Will See You Now E2
programme.desc: Piers Gibbon travels to Peru to try to uncover the science and secrets behind traditional shamanic medicine. Joining Piers in the Amazon jungle are Michael Wudyka with constant shoulder and arm pain and asthma suffer Judith Owens, who experience a range of extreme treatments sourced from the jungle itself. Their mission is to cure their own medical ailments that they have struggled to fix at home.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna S7E6
programme.desc: Following a week when several boats in the fleet partnered up to improve their odds, some of these alliances are still going strong while others are coming apart at the seams. Pinwheel and Fish Hawk continue a fruitful partnership that's keeping both boats at the top of the fleet. But things aren't as smooth for Hot Tuna and Wicked Pissah, as Bubba's tendency to 'overshare' info with the rest of the fleet has Paul giving the Ott's the silent treatment. And while things are looking up for the Dot Com, engine troubles on the Hard Merchandise make them the weak link in a once-promising team-up.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E2
programme.desc: There are only a few days left of deer hunting season in the Blue Ridge Mountains of North Carolina, and homesteaders Tony and Amelia need meat to get them through the cold winter. But Tony has never been deer hunting before and doesn't have the luxury of time to hone his methods. Tony is thrown right in to the hunt, and the pressure is on.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E3
programme.desc: It's trapping season and frontiersman Colbert must get to work. Selling beaver pelts in town will provide him with the bulk of the money to pay the taxes on his land and purchase small items that he cannot get from the swamp. Hunter-gatherer Matt tries hunting rabbits with his new homemade bow and arrow. If he cannot get a source of protein to store for the winter he will need to leave in search of a new shelter.

programme.title: Lawless Island Alaska Compilations S2E4
programme.desc: The newest member of the community, Amanda's story illustrates how the Lawless Island community welcomes newcomers and guides them into self-sustaining Alaskans.

programme.title: One Strange Rock E5
programme.desc: Will we find life like ours on another planet? All life on Earth started as single cell bacteria and stayed like that for 2 billion years. So how did that bacteria become the complex, colorful and diverse life that's all around us? And could this happen anywhere else in the universe? Hosted by astronaut Dr. Mae Jemison.

programme.title: The Witch Doctor Will See You Now E4
programme.desc: Piers Gibbon travels to Cameroon to try to uncover the science and secrets behind traditional Cameroonian medicine. Joining Piers are anxiety sufferer Jenna Patel and Dwight Werner, who has arthritis, back pain and sleep apnea, as they experience a range of extreme treatments. They are on a mission to find a potential cure that Western medicine has been unable to provide.

programme.title: Scrapyard Supercar E7
programme.desc: Ralph and his 2 teams build scrap 4x4 cars which they then race against Shane's Mercedes X Class pick-up in a bone-jarring rock crawl.

programme.title: Facing... E6
programme.desc: From bodybuilder to blockbuster action star to comedy king and then politician, Facing Schwarzenegger explores one of the greatest immigrant success stories of our generation and gives an unabashed look at the life of Arnold Schwarzenegger, an ambitious man who followed his every dream.

programme.title: Outsiders: Living Off The Edge E1
programme.desc: In an ever-shrinking world, there are few corners of the globe that aren't connected to the grid but those places do exist for those determined enough to find them. In the underground caves of the Ozark Mountains lives Joe Ray, while Dan Burton's family live on a small island, Doc and Jeanny Leverett live in a tree house in Washington, and in the mountains of Idaho lives the nomad Bear Claw.

programme.title: Airport Security: Peru E13
programme.desc: On this episode, agents of the Antinarcotics Division of Jorge Chavez International Airport, in Lima, Peru, deal with a case of unique characteristics. In the meantime, officials face language barriers as they detain an Indonesian woman. And a passenger is carrying what seem to be adorable baby blankets, but they are really full of narcotics. At the loading docks, a shipment containing 24 jars puts the drug-detecting dogs' keen sense of smell to the test. Plus, the international flight rush hour results in 2 young passengers being detained side by side at the antinarcotics division headquarters.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E20
programme.desc: Pablo's belief that magic happens in the most unexpected places was just reaffirmed after this trip to the North East of India. Discovering ingredients and flavors that he had never heard of, never tasted or never even imagined existed came into his way. To add to all of this, the wonderful people of North East left no stone unturned to open their hearts and kitchens for Pablo.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E7
programme.desc: Clarke continues his adventure in Samoa. Hunting an elusive Dog Tooth tuna for Chef John, he encounters many other fish along the way including a huge Blue Marlin. He also has a chance to explore more the Island discovering a huge secret family cave with an incredible history many hundreds of years old.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E8
programme.desc: Clarke heads off on a South Island, NZ driving adventure. See him learning more about New Zealand's indigenous Dolphin population and the threat it faces. He also explores local waterways learning about the importance of clean local water ways to Maori before tackling wild Salmon in South Island's famous canals.

programme.title: Places We Go S8E3
programme.desc: Clint explores the world famous Rockies as part of the Icefields Parkway including Athabasca Glacier, Lake Louise and Banff.

programme.title: Route Awakening S3E4
programme.desc: Dr Jonathan Clements, historian, author and TV host, meets the little known Lisu ethnic minority and gets himself into Lisu courtship and wedding but also learns about manly activities like making crossbows, playing musical instruments and climbing a ladder of upturned knives.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted S1E5
programme.desc: Chef Ramsay travels to the Island of Maui, Hawaii, to explore the secrets of Hawaiian cuisine along the rugged Hana coastline.

programme.title: My Pacific Quest E6
programme.desc: After months at sea, adventurer Ellis Emmett's epic Pacific voyages lands him in the island nation of Kiribati, where he comes face-to-face with the realities of climate change, helps get a traditional sailing canoe back into the water, and befriends a king!

programme.title: Ugly House To Lovely House With George Clarke S2E3
programme.desc: Martyn and Sally are desperate to transform their totally impractical 1980's upside down house. Dominated by a big double garage this mishmash of living spaces is so badly laid out that to get from the kitchen to the garden you have to go through the master bedroom. Not ideal for a family that love to barbeque. George teams them up with innovative architect Greg Blee. Greg has recently been busy designing lavish million pound projects in the Caribbean. Can he turn his talents to something much smaller, and will he be able to create a design that works on Martyn and Sally's budget of just £65,000?

programme.title: John Torode's Asia E4
programme.desc: In today's Asian adventure John Torode finds himself in the bustling metropolis of Hong Kong looking for traditional dishes to delight his pallet. John's first stop is the Long Kwai Fong district where he explores the markets with new friend Silvana. Spurred on by the potential for healthy eating, John is taken to an eatery that claims to improve your chances for a long life.

programme.title: Jose Andres: Dinner In Haiti
programme.desc: Join world-renowned chef Jose Andres on an exploration of Haiti, the most unknown country in the Caribbean. Along the way Andres experiences the authentic Haiti's traditions and rituals, from making cassava bread to midnight gatherings with vodou priests, and through its unique cuisine he discovers the history and culture, and sees into the future, of a proud and rarely understood people.

programme.title: Island Hunter E4
programme.desc: Puerto Rico is one of the most popular vacation destinations for Americans, and it's easy to see why; everyone speaks English, it's easy to get to, and of course, it's still a part of the US! Host Liesel Hlista starts off her journey with a goal to feel at one with herself and the best way to do that is with a stint of yoga, atop a paddleboard. SUP yoga! Feeling centered, she begins exploring the island by taking a very detailed walking historical tour as well as a food tour. Bouncing around cantinas and trying out slushy drinks made with the local Don Q rum, Liesel gets a unique insight into old San Juan. To step up the action, Liesel also explores all the hands-on activities such as riding horseback on the beach, riding ATV's through the muddy swamps, and hiking through the super lush El Yunque rainforest. programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E10
programme.desc: Kolkata is home to India's largest Chinese community, which has been in existence for over 200 years, leaving a huge impact on the local food scene. They are fiercely proud of their Hakka-style cuisine and David can't wait to get his fill. He spends the day with a family that produces and sells their own Chinese sauce, eating their delicious momos and fried chicken.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E11
programme.desc: David finally fulfills his dream of visiting the Golden Temple, the holiest Sikh gurudwara in the world. Later, David takes a local food tour to sample all of the local Punjabi delicacies.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S2E6
programme.desc: In this episode of Miguel's Feasts Miguel goes to boot camp in New Zealand for a soldier's treat and shows us the secret to perfect roast chicken!

programme.title: Taiwan: Tropic Of Extremes

He will also tick off his bucket list which includes parkour, fly boarding, kayaking, paragliding and rock climbing.

programme.title: Easyjet: Inside The Cockpit S1E3
programme.desc: 31yr old Adrian swaps his arctic lorry for an Airbus with 186 passengers on board including his parents and twin brother. Meanwhile in New Zealand, after 7 months in the classroom 25 years old Nick is about to take his first solo flight.

programme.title: What's For Sale With A View S2E4

programme.title: Places We Go S8E4
programme.desc: The take in the very best of the Kimberley and dodge a few crocodiles in the process at Bell Gorge, Windjana Gorge & Tunnel Creek.

programme.title: Shark Men S3E11
programme.desc: In the final days of the Cocos Island expedition, the Shark Men are in a race against the clock. The crane dies and Denny disappears. With only hours to go to implant the crucial tags, will the Shark Men pull through?

These rays are said to grow to the size of small trucks. If true, this would be the largest fresh water fish ever.
